notes.note:
New GAP Claim - 217420 - Singh 
Wayne Cheng<Wayne.Cheng@nbfc.com>
​Sean Terkildsen;
​Michael Rocchi <mrocchi@awninsurance.ca>
​Specialty Risk Claims <Specialty.RiskClaims@nbfc.com>
​Hi Sean and Michael,
I just received word from our Legal team pursuant to a review of the GAP policy wordings. 
In this matter, Legal has determined that lenders do not have standing to make a claim under the GAP policy on behalf of insureds.  Therefore, our position is that we are not obligated to provide the National Bank of Canada, or any other lenders, any claims form to initiate a GAP claim.  GAP claims will need to be initiated by insureds, as the only right that lenders have is the receipt of the proceeds/payment for any potential GAP claims.
Please advise the National Bank of Canada that this GAP claim will be required to be initiated by the insured, Sukhjinder Singh.
Thank you,
Wayne Cheng

notes.note:
Customer had emergency repair. VVT solenoids failed. Vehicle went into limp mode.
Pay Customer.
Thanks for your email.
Typically, unauthorized repairs are not covered by the warranty however, we will make an exception in this case and Canada General will cover the repair to the variable valve timing solenoids. The fuel injection flush is not covered and the claim is subject to a $100.00 deductible.
The payout is:
Parts-$290.25
Labour-$111.96 (Mitchell labour guide time of 0.8 hours X $139.95)
Deductible-$100.00
HST-$39.29
Total = $341.50
Please confirm your current mailing address to send the reimbursement cheque to.

Sincerely,
Adam Halko
Claims Manager
